---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import FAQItem from "../components/FAQItem.astro";
---

<Layout title="Help · Subbun" description="Setup, troubleshooting, and frequently asked questions for Subbun.">
  <section class="container-tight py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-2">Help</h1>
    <p class="text-ink-muted mb-10">
      Setup, troubleshooting, and frequently asked questions. Email
      <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2">support@getsubbun.com</a>
      if you can't find your answer here.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-12">Getting started</h2>

    <FAQItem q="How do I install Subbun?">
      <p>
        Go to the Chrome Web Store listing, click "Add to Chrome," and confirm
        the permissions prompt. The first time you open a Japanese video on a
        supported site, Subbun will warm up the on-device AI model (a few
        seconds) and then translations appear automatically.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="Why aren't English subtitles appearing?">
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Confirm the platform's Japanese captions are turned on (the CC button on the player). Subbun reads those captions; it doesn't transcribe audio.</li>
        <li>Confirm your Chrome version is 138 or newer. Open <code>chrome://version</code> to check.</li>
        <li>On first use, the Japanese→English language pack may still be downloading. A progress banner appears in the top-right.</li>
        <li>Some Japanese sites have no caption track at all — Subbun has nothing to read in that case.</li>
      </ul>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="What sites does Subbun work on?">
      <p>
        Free tier: YouTube. Pro tier unlocks Netflix, Amazon Prime, Abema,
        Niconico, Crunchyroll, TVer, NHK Plus, U-NEXT, Disney+, and Hulu Japan
        (11 sites total). If your favorite JP site isn't on the list, email us
        and we'll prioritize it.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-16">Subscriptions and licenses</h2>

    <FAQItem q="Where do I get my license key?">
      <p>
        After purchase, Lemon Squeezy emails you the license key. Paste it
        into the popup. Activation is instant once the key is valid.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="How do I activate Pro on a new computer?">
      <p>
        Install the extension on the new computer, open the popup, paste the
        same license key. Each license supports up to three active devices.
        If you've maxed out, deactivate one of your existing devices via its
        popup, then activate the new one.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="How do I cancel my subscription?">
      <p>
        Click the "Manage subscription" link in the receipt Lemon Squeezy
        emailed you. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current
        billing period; you keep Pro until then. Or email
        <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com">support@getsubbun.com</a> and we'll
        do it for you.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="What's the refund policy?">
      <p>
        No-questions refunds within 60 days of purchase, via Lemon Squeezy.
        Email <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com">support@getsubbun.com</a> with
        your order number and we'll process it.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-16">Translation quality</h2>

    <FAQItem q="What's Quality mode?">
      <p>
        A toggle in the popup that makes the extension use only
        Gemini Nano (highest quality) and skip the basic Translator API
        fallback. When the LLM is busy or recovering from an error, some
        lines will have no subtitle rather than a clunky one. Recommended for
        anime / drama viewers who care about translation quality. Default is
        off — most viewers prefer "every line gets a subtitle" over "every
        line is polished."
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="The translation got a character name wrong. How do I fix it?">
      <p>
        Open the popup → Glossary textbox. Add one line per name you want
        pinned, in this format: <code>悟空 → Goku</code>. Future translations
        will always render that name exactly as you specify. Useful for
        anime and drama where the same characters appear across many episodes.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="Honorifics like -san or -chan are missing.">
      <p>
        Subbun automatically preserves honorifics on properly-detected names.
        If they're getting dropped on a specific character, add an entry to
        the glossary: <code>田中さん → Tanaka-san</code>. That forces the
        rendering on every line.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-16">Privacy</h2>

    <FAQItem q="Does my subtitle text get sent anywhere?">
      <p>
        No. All translation happens on your device using Chrome's built-in
        AI. Subtitle text never leaves your computer. Full
        details on the <a href="/privacy" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2">privacy policy</a>.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <FAQItem q="How do I opt out of usage stats?">
      <p>
        Open the popup → toggle off "Send anonymous usage stats." The setting
        takes effect immediately and any pending events are dropped without
        sending.
      </p>
    </FAQItem>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-16">Still stuck?</h2>

    <p class="text-ink-muted">
      Email <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2">support@getsubbun.com</a>
      with:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-6 space-y-1 text-ink-muted mt-3 mb-8">
      <li>Your Chrome version (from <code>chrome://version</code>)</li>
      <li>Operating system</li>
      <li>The site and video URL where you're seeing the problem</li>
      <li>A screenshot if anything visual is off</li>
      <li>The console output from DevTools (right-click → Inspect → Console tab) showing any <code>[JP-Translator]</code> lines</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
